  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.XCountVsTime" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Each point is the raw DeltaX from one Raw Input report. Use it to spot horizontal micro-jitter, jumpy outliers, or abnormal spikes during fast swipes.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.YCountVsTime" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Each point is the raw DeltaY from one Raw Input report. Use it to spot vertical noise, outliers, or unnatural spikes during upward and downward motion.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.XYCountVsTime" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Shows DeltaX and DeltaY together for every report. Useful for comparing axis balance and finding single-axis noise, bias, or decoupling problems.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.IntervalVsTime" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Each point is the gap from the previous report. Frequent spikes usually indicate report jitter, dropped packets, wireless instability, or scheduler stalls.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.FrequencyVsTime" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Continuous local-window report-rate estimate anchored at every Raw Input report. It preserves every report position while reducing misleading jumps caused by USB interval jitter.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.XVelocityVsTime" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Horizontal speed estimated from local-window cumulative DeltaX / window time / CPI at every Raw Input report anchor. Use it to judge smoothness and low-to-high speed linearity.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.YVelocityVsTime" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Vertical speed estimated from local-window cumulative DeltaY / window time / CPI at every Raw Input report anchor. Use it to judge single-axis stability at higher speed.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.XYVelocityVsTime" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">X and Y local-window speed estimates anchored to the same Raw Input report events. Useful for comparing axis consistency and high-speed stability.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.PathSpeedVsTime" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Overall path speed estimated at every Raw Input report anchor from local-window path length / window time / CPI. Path length sums sqrt(DeltaX² + DeltaY²) for reports inside the window.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.IntervalHistogram" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Distribution built from every valid report interval in the selected range. Use it to judge clustering near the nominal rate, long tails, and host-observed interval jitter.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.DeltaXHistogram" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Signed distribution built from every Raw Input DeltaX report in the selected range, including zero values. Useful for horizontal quantization, bias, and micro-motion output.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.DeltaYHistogram" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Signed distribution built from every Raw Input DeltaY report in the selected range, including zero values. Useful for vertical quantization, bias, and micro-motion output.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.DeltaMagnitudeHistogram" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Non-negative distribution built from every Raw Input delta magnitude in the selected range. Useful for micro-motion loss, quantization steps, and small-motion output ratio.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.VelocityStats" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Speed Stats Avg {0} m/s | P50 {1} | P95 {2} | P99 {3} | P999 {4} | StdDev {5} | MAD {6} | IQR {7}</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.IntervalStats" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Interval Stats Avg {0} | P50 {1} | P95 {2} | P99 {3} | P999 {4} | StdDev {5} | MAD {6} | IQR {7}</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.FrequencyStats" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Frequency Stats Avg {0} Hz | P50 {1} | P95 {2} | P99 {3} | StdDev {4}</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.CountDispersion" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Residual Dispersion MAD {0} | IQR {1}</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.XSumVsTime" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Cumulative DeltaX over time. The slope reflects sustained horizontal output, while abrupt slope changes, flats, or reversals can reveal skipping or correction.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.YSumVsTime" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Cumulative DeltaY over time. Useful for finding vertical stalls, compensation, or unexpected reversals during longer motion.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.XYSumVsTime" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Cumulative DeltaX and DeltaY together. Useful for checking whether long movement remains smooth, synchronized, and free from single-axis drift.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.XVsY" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Trajectory built from cumulative X and Y position. This is the best view for spotting angle snapping, line correction, wobble, axis bias, or imperfect circles.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.Semantics.TrendLine" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Scatter points are the motion samples used by the current plot; the gray line is a trend estimate used to judge overall stability and direction.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.Semantics.ScatterOnly" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">This plot shows all valid report points as raw samples, without connected lines or stems.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.Semantics.RawConnected" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">This plot locks the raw cumulative connected line on: every valid point is drawn, with no sampling or dropped points.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.Semantics.ContinuousEstimate" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">This plot shows a continuous estimate anchored to all valid report anchors: every valid anchor is drawn, with no sampling or dropped points. Statistics use the same basis as the curve.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.Semantics.Trajectory" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">The trajectory view always shows the raw cumulative path inside the selected range. It is never smoothed, so shape defects and correction are easier to judge.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.Semantics.Distribution" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">This plot is a full-sample distribution view: every selected sample contributes to the distribution. The horizontal axis is not time, so gap overlay is disabled.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.Semantics.HostObserved" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">The time axis reflects host-observed Raw Input arrival behavior, not a device-side hardware clock. It is best used to judge the stability of the full input path.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.Semantics.RobustStats" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">MAD and IQR describe robust dispersion, so isolated spikes do not dominate the stability reading.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.Semantics.TimeBasis.RawCapture" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Uses raw capture time with no pause compression or time compensation.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.Semantics.TimeBasis.LogicalSession" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">The X axis uses logical session time. Pause gaps are compressed so the session remains visually continuous.</String>
  <String x:Key="MousePerformance.Chart.Description.Semantics.GapOverlay" xmlns="clr-namespace:System;assembly=System.Private.CoreLib">Long report intervals are host-observed spans where neighboring Raw Input reports are clearly farther apart, and can come from wireless/USB instability, system scheduling delays, or capture processing delays.</String>
